{{Quote|They had me howling on the scan grid, but they never asked me any questions.|Han Solo|<ref name="SWG">[[Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode V: The Empire Strikes Back'']]</ref>}}
The '''scan grid''' was a piece of [[Mining/Legends|mining]] equipment that was occasionally used for more nefarious purposes, such as [[Torture/Legends|torture]] and interrogation, and as such was sometimes known as an '''interrogation array'''. In some of these instances, the sight of the device was so horrifying to the target that it often yielded the interrogator's desired results without even being switched on.<ref name="CCG">{{CCG|set=Cloud City Limited|cardname=Interrogation Array}}</ref>

==History==
[[File:Scan_Grid.jpg|thumb|200px|left|Han Solo being tortured with a scan grid]]
In [[0 ABY/Legends|0 ABY]] a scan grid was used on [[Kalist VI/Legends|Kalist VI]] by [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Zuud]] to torture [[Jorin Sol]].

In [[3 ABY/Legends|3 ABY]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] used one in [[Cloud City/Legends|Cloud City's]] [[Cloud City Security Tower|security tower]] on [[Bespin/Legends|Bespin]] to torture [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]].<ref name="Episode V" /> This scan grid had been specifically commissioned by Vader for use on Han, with it being designed and tested by the city's [[Ugnaught/Legends|Ugnaught]] engineers.<ref name="TPOV">{{SWGTCG|set=The Price of Victory|cardname=Imperial Torture Device #15768|swglink=Imptorturedevice.jpg}}</ref>

